<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{8}{y}=-{54}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{9}{y}={69}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --6. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{6}}{{9}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{6}}}{{9}}{\left({9}{x}+{8}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{6}}}{{9}}{\left(-{54}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{6}\right)}{x}+{5.3333333333333}{y}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{9}{y}={69}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3.6666666666667}{y}={33}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{33}}{{-{{3.6666666666667}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{8}{\left(-{9}\right)}=-{54}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{\left(-{72}\right)}=-{54}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}=-{54}-{\left(-{72}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}={18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{18}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

